WEBVTT

00:33.794 --> 00:36.958
Welcome back to our study of the book of Proverbs.

00:37.259 --> 00:46.211
And we are in chapter seven, and we're going to read verse 22, all the way through to the end.

00:46.291 --> 00:48.153
We're getting close to the end, believe it or not.

00:48.854 --> 00:54.182
So open up your Bibles to Proverbs, chapter seven, verse 22.

00:56.525 --> 01:00.370
Suddenly he follows her as an ox goes to the slaughter.

01:00.930 --> 01:15.163
are as one in fetters to the discipline of a fool, until an arrow pierces through his liver, as a bird hastens to the snare so he does not know that it will cost him his life.

01:15.183 --> 01:19.267
Now therefore, my sons, listen to me and pay attention to the words of my mouth.

01:19.808 --> 01:22.530
Do not let your heart turn aside to her ways.

01:23.331 --> 01:25.173
Do not stray into her paths.

01:26.214 --> 01:30.578
For many are the victims she has cast down and numerous are all her slain.

01:31.106 --> 01:37.174
Her house is the way to shield descending to the chambers of death.

01:38.655 --> 01:40.057
Okay, let's go to the Lord and prayer.

01:43.742 --> 01:49.269
Father, as we're reaching the close of chapter seven, I pray to your God.

01:53.234 --> 01:56.698
Lord, our words are so feeble.

01:58.921 --> 01:59.762
Your word.

02:02.594 --> 02:04.136
is like a two-edged sword.

02:06.760 --> 02:16.615
Lord, I pray that by the Holy Spirit that you would help the truths of this text to be communicated, Lord, to those who may be listening.

02:19.018 --> 02:29.714
Oh, Father, that they would learn that there is a price to sin and that it can be deadly and it can be eternal.

02:31.138 --> 02:43.455
Father, I pray that you would put your fear in the heart of the hearers, that they would reverence you, that they would be terrified of sin.

02:48.262 --> 02:55.212
Father, please work in Jesus' name.

02:56.894 --> 02:59.698
Amen.

03:00.258 --> 03:11.631
We've looked at this wayward woman and we've drawn from her principles of how the world actually works or attempts to work in the life of the believer.

03:12.291 --> 03:16.596
Now, we're going to look at what happens to someone who listens to the world.

03:17.217 --> 03:26.267
This young man that we just read about, he follows her and it ends up in his ruin, his destruction.

03:27.368 --> 03:28.850
I can tell you young people,

03:30.562 --> 03:31.724
You follow the world.

03:33.065 --> 03:34.968
You follow the opinions of the world.

03:35.028 --> 03:37.832
You turn aside from Christ.

03:37.912 --> 03:39.714
You turn aside from His teaching.

03:41.016 --> 03:42.297
It will bring about your ruin.

03:43.379 --> 03:44.080
It truly will.

03:44.861 --> 03:46.903
You see, here's what you need to understand.

03:47.104 --> 03:52.931
If you think I'm doing this just because I don't know, I like to teach the Bible.

03:53.712 --> 03:54.333
You're wrong.

03:55.655 --> 03:58.098
You see, for me, this is real.

03:59.394 --> 04:05.703
It's a matter of life, death, heaven, hell, truth, a lie.

04:08.386 --> 04:16.157
I'm sure you're, you're familiar of the story of the sort of damocles that it's hanging above someone on a, on a thread.

04:17.339 --> 04:26.692
And in many ways, that's, that's the life of the sinner separated from Christ, following the world at any moment.

04:27.933 --> 04:28.434
That's

04:28.546 --> 04:37.435
Tiny, tiny string that thread can break and the sword comes piercing through to your own destruction.

04:39.557 --> 04:48.625
Borrowing from Jonathan Edwards, we could talk about, you know, how small and weak is the web of a spider when touched by a flame?

04:50.687 --> 04:57.714
Your life without Christ, your life of rebellion and disobedience, you're like a spider.

04:58.370 --> 05:04.478
on a thin web over a blazing fire.

05:05.500 --> 05:11.107
It doesn't even take a touch of a flame and the spider is no more.

05:12.389 --> 05:17.095
There is a real sense in which you ought to fear.

05:18.177 --> 05:23.143
You know, some fear is irrational, completely irrational.

05:24.325 --> 05:26.267
Some fear is not.

05:26.828 --> 05:28.210
It is quite rational.

05:28.354 --> 05:31.058
and very healthy, it can save your life.

05:32.059 --> 05:48.661
And the Bible sets before us the fear of the Lord, a deep and abiding reverence for Him, but also the fear of sin, of what it can do to us, the destruction it can bring about, not only in your life.

05:49.142 --> 05:50.584
Young person, do you realize something?

05:51.986 --> 05:55.190
You say, well, it's my life, doesn't affect anybody else.

05:55.210 --> 05:58.034
That is just not true, that is.

05:58.178 --> 06:01.461
That, that deserves the word stupid because that's what it is.

06:02.702 --> 06:03.343
That's not true.

06:05.766 --> 06:10.350
If my children destroyed themselves, do you think I would not be affected?

06:11.471 --> 06:13.333
Do you think their friends would not be affected?

06:14.634 --> 06:18.218
No, you don't live or die alone to yourself.

06:19.079 --> 06:22.963
What you do has an impact on everyone.

06:22.983 --> 06:24.404
Look at society today.

06:25.906 --> 06:26.386
Okay.

06:26.754 --> 06:40.254
It is a mass of people influencing one another for evil, living a life that is antichrist, that is separated from God.

06:41.315 --> 06:44.860
Each one of them is having an impact on the other.

06:45.201 --> 06:50.909
And what you need to understand is our lives will have an impact for good or for evil.

06:51.490 --> 06:54.354
Now, for some of you who are older, children,

06:54.786 --> 06:59.714
You need to realize what you do is also going to impact your younger siblings.

07:00.435 --> 07:05.303
Because you're older, stronger, smarter, faster, they want to be like you.

07:06.805 --> 07:11.252
You can either set a good example or an evil one.

07:12.414 --> 07:15.900
I could say a bad one, but evil sounds more severe, doesn't it?

07:17.723 --> 07:19.866
So how we live impacts others.

07:19.906 --> 07:22.450
And we're going to see here that this young man

07:22.946 --> 07:25.609
His life turns out to be a cautionary tale.

07:28.693 --> 07:34.380
His life has become a story to warn others not to be like him.

07:35.562 --> 07:38.105
Is that the legacy that you want to live?

07:39.106 --> 07:48.978
Now, this young man's demise, his ruin, what is interesting here, it only takes two verses to describe his ruin.

07:49.250 --> 07:53.034
All this, and we've had verse after verse after verse after verse, what?

07:53.054 --> 08:04.567
21 verses of this lengthy sort of narrative of this life of his, and it just takes two verses, and he's destroyed.

08:05.928 --> 08:06.729
He's destroyed.

08:07.550 --> 08:12.416
And it says in verse 22, it says, suddenly he follows her.

08:13.757 --> 08:15.139
Now I want to read for you something.

08:15.519 --> 08:18.162
One single bad decision.

08:19.490 --> 08:25.158
that takes less than a few seconds will bring his short life to an end.

08:26.200 --> 08:36.595
How many people, how many young people have ruined their entire life with one bad decision?

08:36.615 --> 08:49.074
I remember years and years and years ago, there was this basketball player and everyone thought, man, he is going to be amazing.

08:49.858 --> 08:51.440
in the pros everywhere.

08:51.780 --> 08:58.248
And everyone knew him as a good guy, like he was a nice person to be around.

09:00.931 --> 09:07.859
Right before he, I think he was either recruited or right after he graduated from college and then recruited.

09:08.359 --> 09:11.363
He went to a party, went to one party.

09:11.963 --> 09:17.810
He wasn't known for alcohol, he wasn't known for drugs, he wasn't known for any of that, but he went to a party.

09:18.914 --> 09:26.206
And many say it was the only time, first time he took a drug and he died immediately.

09:27.268 --> 09:31.656
An entire life, one bad decision and he killed him.

09:32.497 --> 09:34.941
One bad decision and it ruined everything.

09:35.782 --> 09:44.978
I told my children this often and with purpose, I told them that do you realize

09:47.938 --> 09:58.714
You can make a bad decision and maybe dad can step in and save you, but there can come a time when you make a bad decision.

09:58.895 --> 10:00.117
You break the law.

10:00.657 --> 10:05.405
You be driving drunk and hurt somebody else.

10:06.346 --> 10:09.010
There's nothing dad can do.

10:09.651 --> 10:14.098
There comes a time when there is absolutely nothing.

10:14.594 --> 10:16.596
that someone else can do to save you.

10:16.916 --> 10:22.562
In fact, there comes a time when even God will not save you.

10:22.923 --> 10:24.144
That's what I told my children.

10:25.285 --> 10:31.231
Now, so it says here in verse 22, suddenly he follows her.

10:32.853 --> 10:34.995
Now here's a really important question.

10:36.076 --> 10:38.458
Who are you going to follow whom?

10:39.459 --> 10:40.581
You're going to follow someone.

10:40.681 --> 10:42.002
I mean, you're not an island.

10:42.562 --> 10:46.848
You're not inventing your life as you go without the influence of others.

10:47.188 --> 10:49.291
You're going to follow someone.

10:49.572 --> 10:53.918
Or if you really want to be hard about it, there are three possibilities.

10:54.999 --> 10:55.921
You follow others.

10:56.241 --> 10:57.363
You follow yourself.

10:57.483 --> 10:58.725
You follow God's word.

10:58.805 --> 10:59.806
Now, which is it going to be?

10:59.846 --> 11:06.215
If you follow others that are going astray, that's not very wise, the Bible says you shouldn't follow yourself.

11:06.375 --> 11:11.282
There's a way that seems right unto men, but it leads to death.

11:12.066 --> 11:13.328
Wisdom wasn't born with you.

11:13.368 --> 11:14.370
It won't die with you.

11:16.133 --> 11:17.335
So you have to make a decision.

11:18.337 --> 11:23.286
And the only wise decision is to follow God as he reveals himself in his word.

11:23.706 --> 11:25.730
But here in verse 22, what do we see?

11:26.291 --> 11:30.438
He follows her a very evil, wicked person.

11:30.679 --> 11:31.761
Now think about this.

11:32.943 --> 11:37.170
She has flattered him and he thinks that she really loves him.

11:37.954 --> 11:39.636
that she'll be faithful to him.

11:39.877 --> 11:44.484
But once you think about something, she wasn't faithful to her husband, she wasn't faithful to her children.

11:45.505 --> 11:48.149
You think that the world's gonna come and be your friend.

11:48.650 --> 11:56.481
No, the world is gonna be your friend as long as it's useful, beneficial, entertaining, pleasurable to the world.

11:56.882 --> 11:58.044
After that, it's all over.

11:58.364 --> 11:59.626
Remember the prodigal son?

12:00.628 --> 12:01.269
I hope you do.

12:02.450 --> 12:07.698
When he went out with his father's inheritance and he just partied like crazy,

12:08.034 --> 12:09.896
Oh, man, did he have the friends?

12:10.417 --> 12:11.999
They all gathered around him.

12:12.119 --> 12:13.782
He was the talk of the town.

12:13.862 --> 12:16.986
He was the focus of everyone's attention until what?

12:17.567 --> 12:18.428
He ran out of money.

12:18.708 --> 12:20.010
They couldn't use him anymore.

12:20.310 --> 12:21.572
Then he just ate with the pigs.

12:22.533 --> 12:22.914
Okay.

12:24.216 --> 12:25.037
So he follows.

12:25.357 --> 12:27.280
How does he follow?

12:27.300 --> 12:30.444
As an ox goes to the slaughter.

12:32.106 --> 12:35.271
Do you know why the ox goes to the slaughter willingly?

12:35.791 --> 12:37.874
Because he doesn't know he's going to the slaughter.

12:38.594 --> 12:41.438
because he's ignorant of the consequences.

12:46.025 --> 12:48.589
Do not be ignorant of the consequences of sin.

12:49.150 --> 12:53.957
Do not let someone deceive you as we've already learned that there are no consequences.

12:54.298 --> 12:54.939
There are.

12:54.999 --> 12:57.623
Listen, child, there are.

12:57.663 --> 13:07.698
I've lived long enough to see so many lives ruined by sin and not just people in the world.

13:07.842 --> 13:09.764
but people who claim to be in Christ.

13:10.785 --> 13:25.181
And I do believe that even true Christians can sometimes push the envelope so much that there's no closing in again, that they do things in their life that bring a lifetime of regret.

13:25.241 --> 13:31.388
She follows him or he follows her like an ox to the slaughter.

13:31.508 --> 13:32.950
You ever seen cattle slaughtered?

13:33.450 --> 13:35.152
I have many of them.

13:35.593 --> 13:36.754
It's not a pretty picture.

13:37.698 --> 13:44.647
and then go on verse 22 as one in fetters to the discipline of a fool.

13:45.047 --> 13:46.329
Now I want you to think about that.

13:48.151 --> 13:54.920
So you have someone that made a decision and now they are in chains.

13:54.940 --> 13:56.101
There's nothing they can do.

13:56.181 --> 13:57.263
There's nothing they can do.

13:57.583 --> 14:01.408
They're being drug to the punishment of a fool.

14:02.709 --> 14:04.612
You say, well, it's not the punishment of a criminal.

14:05.273 --> 14:06.354
It really doesn't matter.

14:07.554 --> 14:08.615
They are a criminal.

14:08.976 --> 14:09.236
Why?

14:09.356 --> 14:10.598
Because they were a fool.

14:10.998 --> 14:11.359
And why?

14:11.559 --> 14:12.420
How are they a fool?

14:12.720 --> 14:16.385
Because they did not listen to God's word, but they listened to the world.

14:16.645 --> 14:22.212
Maybe they didn't listen to their godly parents, but they listened to the world.

14:22.532 --> 14:23.854
Do you see that?

14:23.874 --> 14:24.855
It's really interesting.

14:24.895 --> 14:27.798
There's a version of the Bible called the Syriac version.

14:28.900 --> 14:31.163
It's it's second century, very old.

14:31.483 --> 14:34.066
And it says this, like a stag.

14:34.306 --> 14:37.729
prancing into a trapper's snare.

14:38.270 --> 14:45.016
So like a stag, a big deer, an elk, something like that, just prancing.

14:46.558 --> 14:52.263
All excited, all happy, and then all of a sudden, wam, the snare, right there.

14:52.924 --> 14:53.505
Do you see that?

14:54.566 --> 14:55.607
And that's the same way.

14:56.728 --> 15:02.293
I'm gonna be honest with you, some people are this world, according to 1 John, and we may look at it later.

15:02.733 --> 15:03.314
It's like,

15:03.490 --> 15:10.681
a parade of clowns banging symbols and just walking off a cliff.

15:11.883 --> 15:14.246
That's the idea that's being communicated here.

15:15.508 --> 15:16.249
Now let's go on.

15:16.790 --> 15:18.513
There's another description here.

15:20.015 --> 15:28.828
It says, suddenly follows her as an ox goes to the slaughter or as one in the fetters to the discipline of a fool.

15:30.891 --> 15:32.754
In verse 23, look what it says.

15:33.090 --> 15:36.573
as a bird hastens to the snare.

15:38.055 --> 15:43.540
He runs quickly and stupidly to the bait.

15:43.900 --> 15:48.345
You know, when we talk about a bird brain, we're not talking about someone who's a genius, are we?

15:48.585 --> 15:52.188
We're talking about someone who has no sense at all.

15:53.229 --> 15:57.573
Even the largest birds in the world have a very, very small brain.

15:58.194 --> 16:02.418
The fool that does not listen to the word of God is basically

16:02.978 --> 16:11.150
a bird brain who runs straight to a bait, not thinking at all about the path of his feet.

16:11.330 --> 16:12.632
And it ends in destruction.

16:13.313 --> 16:19.322
But you know, we can remember when we studied Proverbs chapter one, it says even a bird.

16:19.462 --> 16:20.143
Well, let me read it.

16:20.204 --> 16:21.846
Proverbs one, 17 and 18.

16:21.886 --> 16:29.938
Indeed, it is useless to spread the baited net in the sight of any bird, but they fools evil people.

16:30.146 --> 16:31.968
lie and wait for their own blood.

16:32.248 --> 16:33.790
They ambush their own lives.

16:35.973 --> 16:37.034
I want you to think about that.

16:41.419 --> 16:42.180
What is a fool?

16:43.221 --> 16:45.563
Is a fool someone who is not intelligent?

16:46.464 --> 16:46.705
No.

16:47.606 --> 16:49.888
Is a fool someone who has a very low IQ?

16:49.948 --> 16:50.609
No.

16:53.132 --> 16:58.418
A fool is someone who ignores God's word

17:01.634 --> 17:02.675
They don't care to learn it.

17:03.356 --> 17:07.040
And even what they know, they don't obey.

17:08.342 --> 17:15.950
Now, I want us to look at 1 John chapter 2 verse 11.

17:15.970 --> 17:20.695
How does someone become this foolish?

17:22.357 --> 17:23.519
I mean, what's going on here?

17:23.799 --> 17:30.226
If you go to 1 John 2, 11, it describes the sinner as one who is in the darkness,

17:30.466 --> 17:39.057
and walks in the darkness and does not know where he is going because the darkness has blinded his eyes.

17:40.038 --> 17:45.265
He doesn't know where he's going because he is in darkness.

17:46.306 --> 17:53.195
Now, we could go into all kinds of things with this passage, but I just want one thing to stick in your mind.

17:54.617 --> 17:58.322
If you are not in God's Word,

17:59.234 --> 18:08.143
If you're not believing in Christ, if you're not studying God's Word, you're in darkness.

18:08.583 --> 18:09.584
And that's all there is to it.

18:10.265 --> 18:14.369
Because as we're going to see, the Bible is the light.

18:15.410 --> 18:22.837
Knowing Christ brings light and studying the Scriptures bring light.

18:24.318 --> 18:28.242
Now you may say, Brother Paul, I go to church, you know,

18:28.386 --> 18:29.848
My family's Christian.

18:29.868 --> 18:32.992
All right, wonderful.

18:34.894 --> 18:35.735
Let me ask you a question.

18:35.775 --> 18:37.618
How much time do you spend in the scriptures?

18:38.759 --> 18:40.401
You say, well, I'm eight.

18:41.483 --> 18:41.923
I don't care.

18:41.963 --> 18:45.588
You can read, can't you?

18:47.110 --> 18:49.112
How much time are you in the scriptures?

18:50.254 --> 18:53.157
Child, you want to be something that very few people are.

18:55.520 --> 18:56.722
Devote yourself.

18:57.186 --> 18:58.647
Not to the reading of good books.

19:01.110 --> 19:02.951
Devote yourself to the reading of the book.

19:04.333 --> 19:04.813
The Bible.

19:05.434 --> 19:11.139
From Genesis to Revelation, over and over and over and over and over again.

19:11.179 --> 19:12.861
Until you're like John Bunyan.

19:13.421 --> 19:14.682
You know what Spurgeon said about him?

19:15.023 --> 19:18.166
If you cut him, he would bleed the blind.

19:18.806 --> 19:19.447
Know what that means?

19:19.547 --> 19:20.428
He'd bleed the Bible.

19:21.309 --> 19:22.710
He was running through his veins.

19:23.090 --> 19:27.154
Oh, if God would raise up a generation, not just of young men,

19:27.554 --> 19:36.465
But if young women who know the word, then we would have a lot of people walking in the light.

19:37.786 --> 19:49.821
I want you to listen to what David said, Psalms 119, 104, 105, or what the psalmist said, from your precepts, I get understanding.

19:50.922 --> 19:54.226
Therefore I hate every false way.

19:54.786 --> 19:58.351
Your word is a lamp to my feet and a light to my path.

19:59.132 --> 19:59.833
Isn't that amazing?

20:00.394 --> 20:01.435
Let's listen to it again.

20:01.475 --> 20:06.402
From your precepts, from what is written in the scriptures, okay?

20:06.422 --> 20:13.191
Not from dreams, not from visions, not from opinions, and not even from good sermons as important as they are.

20:13.632 --> 20:13.872
No.

20:14.413 --> 20:18.738
From directly reading the scriptures, I get understanding.

20:18.999 --> 20:19.960
Now let's reverse that.

20:20.341 --> 20:22.684
If you're not reading the scriptures, you don't have understanding.

20:24.206 --> 20:24.306
Okay?

20:25.378 --> 20:26.499
That's just the way it is.

20:26.539 --> 20:29.323
And we, there's no need to argue about it.

20:31.746 --> 20:33.969
You get understanding from God's scripture.

20:34.529 --> 20:40.116
If you ignore God's scripture, you don't have understanding, at least not in the things that are important.

20:41.017 --> 20:44.481
He says, from your precepts, I get understanding.

20:44.622 --> 20:49.388
Therefore, when you read the Bible, you get understanding.

20:49.528 --> 20:51.851
And when you get understanding, you know what you do.

20:52.191 --> 20:54.674
You hate everything that's false.

20:55.618 --> 20:58.847
And you love everything that is true.

20:58.887 --> 21:02.978
You actually hate things.

21:02.998 --> 21:07.410
You can identify things that are false and you hate them.

21:08.642 --> 21:17.453
because your heart has been transformed by the Spirit of God and the Word of God and your brain has been renewed with the Word of God and the Spirit of God.

21:17.733 --> 21:20.256
And therefore you're thinking like Christ thinks.

21:20.637 --> 21:25.823
And the Bible says of the Messiah that he hated lawlessness and he loved righteousness.

21:26.764 --> 21:27.064
Okay?

21:27.805 --> 21:29.027
I hate every false way.

21:29.347 --> 21:34.093
Now he's going to reiterate how is it that he gets understanding?

21:34.413 --> 21:38.418
He says, your Word is a lamp to my feet and a light

21:38.882 --> 21:41.765
to my path.

21:44.929 --> 21:46.290
Man, I used to hunt in this place.

21:47.071 --> 21:51.235
When I was a boy, it was really what we called swampy.

21:52.557 --> 21:56.601
And we had this, what we called a water moccasin or a cotton mouth.

21:57.622 --> 22:01.106
And there are some poisonous snakes that you gotta admit, they're beautiful.

22:01.346 --> 22:02.488
This thing is not.

22:03.148 --> 22:05.091
It's as ugly as it is mean.

22:05.271 --> 22:06.672
It looks like a big slug.

22:07.413 --> 22:08.274
They're fat.

22:08.546 --> 22:11.290
They're big and they will chase you.

22:11.871 --> 22:20.345
And as a little boy, you know, I got to where I could walk pretty well in the moonlight or in the early morning when there was just a little bit of light.

22:20.826 --> 22:28.018
But man, when it was pitch darkness, you either did not walk through there or you walk through there with some sort of a light.

22:29.520 --> 22:29.861
Okay.

22:31.584 --> 22:33.106
Because those things are dangerous.

22:35.618 --> 22:37.580
We call them two steppers.

22:37.600 --> 22:40.002
They bite you and you take two steps and fall over.

22:41.263 --> 22:43.265
So you needed a light in there.

22:44.306 --> 22:50.713
You need light because the serpent that you're dealing with is far more dangerous than a cotton mouth or water moccasin.

22:52.454 --> 22:58.400
Serpent's you're dealing with can bite you and bring about eternal death.

22:59.121 --> 23:03.105
So you need the light of God's word.

23:03.966 --> 23:04.466
All right.

23:05.026 --> 23:06.307
All right, let's go to the Lord in prayer.

23:08.630 --> 23:22.366
Father, thank you for your word, and I pray that you would use it, dear God, in the heart of those who are listening.

23:24.148 --> 23:33.138
Oh, dear God, I think about the precious children, teenagers, how smart they may think that they are and how

23:38.114 --> 23:41.702
how novice they actually are.

23:41.722 --> 23:53.367
Please, Lord God, put in their hearts, their minds, the fear of the Lord, that they would know Christ and know the Scriptures and walk in that light.

23:54.009 --> 23:56.434
In Jesus name, amen.

